Package com.dua3.meja.model

Interface Workbook

All Superinterfaces:
AutoCloseable, Iterable<Sheet>
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractWorkbook, GenericWorkbook, PoiWorkbook, PoiWorkbook.PoiHssfWorkbook, PoiWorkbook.PoiXssfWorkbook
public interface Workbook extends AutoCloseable, Iterable<Sheet>
Workbook class.

A workbook consists of different sheets which can be accessed by number or name. Use one of the concrete implementations of WorkbookFactory to read a workbook from disk.

    • isObjectCachingEnabled

      boolean isObjectCachingEnabled()
      Test whether object caching is enabled.
      Returns:
      state of object caching

    • setObjectCaching

      void setObjectCaching(boolean enable)
      Set object caching.
      When object caching is enabled, cell values will be added to a simple cache. This helps to reduce memory consumption when adding many instances to a workbook that are technically equal. A good example is adding calculated dates to a workbook with many cells containing instances representing the same values. The effect on memory consumption may vary between different workbook implementations. When in doubt, measure with realistic data for your use case.
      Parameters:
      enable - flag indicating whether to en- or disable object caching

    • write

      default void write(URI uri, com.dua3.utility.options.Arguments options, DoubleConsumer updateProgress) throws IOException
      Writes the workbook to a file at the given URI with the specified options, and updates the progress using the provided DoubleConsumer.
      Parameters:
      uri - the URI to write to.

      The file format to used is determined by the extension of uri which must be one of the extensions defined in FileType.

      options - special options to use (supported options depend on the file type)
      updateProgress - the consumer that will receive the progress value (a double between 0 and 1) periodically during the writing process
      Throws:
      IOException - if an I/O error occurs
      IllegalArgumentException - if the file type for the given URI cannot be determined

    • write

      default void write(Path path, com.dua3.utility.options.Arguments options, DoubleConsumer updateProgress) throws IOException
      Writes the workbook to a file with progress update.
      Parameters:
      path - the path to write to.

      The file format to used is determined by the extension of uri which must be one of the extensions defined in FileType.

      options - special options to use (supported options depend on the file type)
      updateProgress - a consumer that accepts a double value representing the progress of the write operation, where 0.0 indicates no progress and 1.0 indicates completion.
      Throws:
      IOException - if an I/O error occurs
      IllegalArgumentException - if the file type cannot be determined for the given path
